## Design system structure (agent checklist)

Answers the Figma MCP `create_design_system_rules` template for this repo.

1. **Token definitions:** `:root` and `[data-theme="dark"]` in `assets/css/style.css`. Machine-readable mirror: repo-root **`FIGMA_TOKENS.json`** (Tokens Studio shape). No Style Dictionary / CI transform pipeline—tokens are edited in CSS and kept in sync with Figma manually or via Tokens Studio.

2. **Component library:** No React/Vue component tree. **Layout chrome** = string builders in `assets/js/layout-components.js` (`LayoutComponents.*`). **Page chrome** = `PortfolioApp` + `pageData` in `assets/js/components.js`. **Visible UI** = HTML in `*.html` (`#page-specific-content`) + shared classes in `style.css`. **Local plugin:** `figma-plugin/code.js` can generate a reference frame (uses **Inter** in code; live site uses **Montserrat**—align fonts when comparing).

3. **Frameworks & libraries:** Vanilla JS, no bundler. **Font Awesome 6.4** via CDN from `injectHead()` in `components.js`. Optional **Lenis** smooth scroll. **Cursor:** `assets/js/cursor.js`, `assets/css/cursor.css`.

4. **Asset management:** Static files under `assets/img/` (including `assets/img/main images/` for grid thumbnails). Paths are **relative to site root**. No CDN for images except Google Fonts and Font Awesome.

5. **Icon system:** Font Awesome classes in HTML (`fas`, `far`, etc.). No local SVG sprite for UI chrome; project/case imagery is raster/SVG under `assets/img/`.

6. **Styling approach:** Global CSS + variables; page-specific `assets/css/<page>.css` or scoped `<style>` in HTML for one-off case studies. Responsive behavior via **`@media` in `style.css`** (not container queries by default).

7. **Project structure:** Multi-page static site: `index.html`, `about.html`, `playground.html`, per-project `*.html`. Shared behavior: `assets/js/index.js`, `layout-components.js`, `components.js`. **Code Connect:** this stack does not map 1:1 to published React components; prefer documenting class names / builders or Markdown links unless the team adds a component framework.

